(93, 45, 'product_s_desc', 'SolEpoxy DK15-02 is a blow-coat brown epoxy coating powder developed for electrical insulation of toroids, current transformers, magnetic and powder cores.\r\n\r\nEpoxy-coated or impregnated magnetic and powder cores can be blow-coated or dipped into a fluidized bed for maximum edge coverage. It offers excellent cut-through temperature resistance with good edge coverage and is UL recognized for 130ºC operating temperature.', '<p>SolEpoxy™ DK15-02 Brown is an epoxy based coating powder developed as an epoxy resin binder when making pot-core type reactors or induction devices.  The principal fields of application of pot-type cores that use DK15-02 Brown include:\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Storage chokes for switch-mode power supplies</li>\r\n<li>Storage chokes for DC regulators and power factor controllers</li>\r\n<li>Commutation chokes for feedback capable frequency inverters</li>\r\n<li>Output chokes for traction inverters</li>\r\n<li>dU/dt limiting chokes</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SolEpoxy™ DK15-02 Brown is also used for electrical insulation of toroids, current transformers, magnetic and powder cores.  The advantage of DK15-02 Brown in these cases is that it can be blow-coated.  As a toroid or current transformer coating, it offers cut-through temperature resistance with good edge coverage and is UL recognized for 130ºC operating temperature.   Though DK15-02 Brown was designed to be applied via a blow coating process and can be also be applied via a standard fluid bed process in most applications.</p>'),
