(438, 247, 'product_s_desc', '<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ Electrically Conductive Plastic Sheeting is a black, carbon-filled, volume-conductive polyethylene film designed to provide both physical and static protection.  The family is made up of LINQSTAT XVCF-Series which is a high-level electrically conductive plastic with a surface resistance of 100 ohm-cm (10^2 Ω-cm) and LINQSTAT VCF-Series which is a mid-level electrically conductive plastic having a surface resistance of 10,000 ohm-cm (10^4 Ω-cm).</p>\r\n<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ XVCF-Series and VCF-Series conductive films and their conductivity are unaffected by humidity and age.  The film is heat-sealable, flexible and offers exceptional abrasion resistance.  The film gives good thermal stability and has outstanding chemical resistance. It has a standard thickness range from 65μm to 200μm (0.0025” to 0.008”) and is available in sheeting, tubing, V-fold and C-fold versions.  Roll lengths and widths vary depending on thickness and application.</p>', '<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ Electrically Conductive Plastic Sheeting is a black, carbon-filled, volume-conductive polyethylene film designed to provide both physical and static protection.  The family is made up of LINQSTAT XVCF-Series which is a high-level electrically conductive plastic with a surface resistance of 100 ohm-cm (10^2 Ω-cm) and LINQSTAT VCF-Series which is a mid-level electrically conductive plastic having a surface resistance of 10,000 ohm-cm.</p>\r\n<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ XVCF-Series and VCF-Series conductive films and their conductivity are unaffected by humidity and age.  The film is heat-sealable, flexible and offers exceptional abrasion resistance.  The film gives good thermal stability and has outstanding chemical resistance. It has a standard thickness range from 65 micron to 200 micron (2.5 mil 8 mil) and is available in sheeting, tubing, V-fold and C-fold versions.  Roll lengths and widths vary depending on thickness and application.</p>'),
(439, 248, 'product_s_desc', 'CAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ XVCF-Series is a black, carbon-filled, volume-conductive polyethylene film designed to provide both physical and static protection.  Having a surface resistance of less than 100 ohm-cm, (10^2 Ω-cm) it offers high-level static protection and excellent conductivity for application that require a lower resistance (higher conductivity) than LINQSTAT VCF-Series films.\r\n\r\nCAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ XVCF-Series is useful in applications where the key is to maximize the conductivity in a polyethylene dielectric by optimizing the carbon loading.  As a high-level conductive plastic, the carbon-loading is such that it is high-enough to meet the electrical requirements needed for applications such as electrodes and pressure sensors.\r\n\r\nCAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ XVCF-Series film and its conductivity are unaffected by humidity and age.  The film is heat-sealable, flexible and offers exceptional abrasion resistance.  The film gives good thermal stability and has outstanding chemical resistance. It has a standard thickness range from 65μm to 100μm (2.5 mil to 4 mil) and is available in sheeting, tubing, or bag versions.  Roll lengths and widths vary depending on thickness and application.', 'CAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ XVCF-Series is a black, carbon-filled, volume-conductive polyethylene film designed to provide both physical and static protection.  Having a surface resistance of less than 100 ohm-cm, it offers high-level static protection and excellent conductivity for application that require a lower resistance (higher conductivity) than LINQSTAT VCF-Series films.\r\n\r\nCAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ XVCF-Series is useful in applications where the key is to maximize the conductivity in a polyethylene dielectric by optimizing the carbon loading.  As a high-level conductive plastic, the carbon-loading is such that it is high-enough to meet the electrical requirements needed for applications such as electrodes and pressure sensors.\r\n\r\nCAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ XVCF-Series film and its conductivity are unaffected by humidity and age.  The film is heat-sealable, flexible and offers exceptional abrasion resistance.  The film gives good thermal stability and has outstanding chemical resistance. It has a standard thickness range from 65 micron to 100 micron (2.5 mil to 4 mil) and is available in sheeting, tubing, or bag versions.  Roll lengths and widths vary depending on thickness and application.'),
