(463, 260, 'product_s_desc', 'CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is a black, carbon-filled, volume-conductive polyethylene film designed to provide both physical and static protection.  Having a surface resistance of less than 100 ohm-cm, it offers high-level static protection and excellent conductivity for application that require a lower resistance (higher conductivity) than LINQSTAT VCF-Series films.CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is useful in applications where the key is to maximize the conductivity in a polyethylene dielectric by optimizing the carbon loading.  As a high-level conductive plastic, the carbon-loading is such that it is high-enough to meet the electrical requirements needed for applications such as electrodes and pressure sensors.CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series film and its conductivity are unaffected by humidity and age.  The film is heat-sealable, flexible and offers exceptional abrasion resistance.  The film gives good thermal stability and has outstanding chemical resistance. It has a standard thickness range from 65 micron to 100 micron (2.5 mil to 4 mil) and is available in sheeting, tubing, or bag versions.  Roll lengths and widths vary depending on thickness and application.', '<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is a black, carbon-filled, volume-conductive polyethylene film designed to provide both physical and static protection.  Having a surface resistance of less than 100 ohms per square (10E2 Ω/square) , it offers high-level static protection and excellent conductivity for application that require a lower resistance (higher conductivity) than LINQSTAT VCF-Series (Surface Resistance < 10E5 Ω/sq) or LINQSTAT MVCF-Series (Surface Resistance < 10E4 Ω/sq) films.  CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is useful in applications where the key is to maximize the conductivity in a polyethylene dielectric by optimizing the carbon loading.  As a high-level conductive plastic, the carbon-loading is such that it is high-enough to meet the electrical requirements needed for applications such as electrodes and pressure sensors.</p><p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series film and its conductivity are unaffected by humidity and age.  The film is heat-sealable, flexible and offers exceptional abrasion resistance.  The film gives good thermal stability and has outstanding chemical resistance. It has a standard thickness range from 65 micron to 100 micron (2.5 mil to 4 mil) and is available in sheeting, tubing, or bag versions.  Roll lengths and widths vary depending on thickness and application.</p>\r\n<h2>Applications for High-Level Electrically Conductive Plastic</h2><p>LINQSTAT XVCF-Series sheeting can be used for TENS Electrodes manufacturing as well as high-level precision pressure sensors.</p>'),
(464, 261, 'product_s_desc', '<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is a black, carbon-filled, volume-conductive polyethylene film designed to provide both physical and static protection.  Having a surface resistance of less than 100 ohms per square (10E2 ?/square) , it offers high-level static protection and excellent conductivity for application that require a lower resistance (higher conductivity) than LINQSTAT VCF-Series (Surface Resistance < 10E5 ?/sq) or LINQSTAT MVCF-Series (Surface Resistance < 10E4 ?/sq) films.  CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is useful in applications where the key is to maximize the conductivity in a polyethylene dielectric by optimizing the carbon loading.  As a high-level conductive plastic, the carbon-loading is such that it is high-enough to meet the electrical requirements needed for applications such as electrodes and pressure sensors.</p><p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series film and its conductivity are unaffected by humidity and age.  The film is heat-sealable, flexible and offers exceptional abrasion resistance.  The film gives good thermal stability and has outstanding chemical resistance. It has a standard thickness range from 65 micron to 100 micron (2.5 mil to 4 mil) and is available in sheeting, tubing, or bag versions.  Roll lengths and widths vary depending on thickness and application.</p>\n<h2>Applications for High-Level Electrically Conductive Plastic</h2><p>LINQSTAT XVCF-Series sheeting can be used for TENS Electrodes manufacturing as well as high-level precision pressure sensors.</p>', '<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is a black, carbon-filled, volume-conductive polyethylene film designed to provide both physical and static protection.  Having a surface resistance of less than 100 ohms per square (10E2 Ω/square) , it offers high-level static protection and excellent conductivity for application that require a lower resistance (higher conductivity) than LINQSTAT VCF-Series (Surface Resistance < 10E5 Ω/sq) or LINQSTAT MVCF-Series (Surface Resistance < 10E4 Ω/sq) films.  CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is useful in applications where the key is to maximize the conductivity in a polyethylene dielectric by optimizing the carbon loading.  As a high-level conductive plastic, the carbon-loading is such that it is high-enough to meet the electrical requirements needed for applications such as electrodes and pressure sensors.</p><p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series film and its conductivity are unaffected by humidity and age.  The film is heat-sealable, flexible and offers exceptional abrasion resistance.  The film gives good thermal stability and has outstanding chemical resistance. It has a standard thickness range from 65 micron to 100 micron (2.5 mil to 4 mil) and is available in sheeting, tubing, or bag versions.  Roll lengths and widths vary depending on thickness and application.</p>\r\n<h2>Applications for High-Level Electrically Conductive Plastic</h2><p>LINQSTAT XVCF-Series sheeting can be used for TENS Electrodes manufacturing as well as high-level precision pressure sensors.</p>'),
(465, 262, 'product_s_desc', '<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is a black, carbon-filled, volume-conductive polyethylene film designed to provide both physical and static protection.  Having a surface resistance of less than 100 ohms per square (10E2 Ω/square) , it offers high-level static protection and excellent conductivity for application that require a lower resistance (higher conductivity) than LINQSTAT VCF-Series (Surface Resistance < 10E5 Ω/sq) or LINQSTAT MVCF-Series (Surface Resistance < 10E4 Ω/sq) films.  CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is useful in applications where the key is to maximize the conductivity in a polyethylene dielectric by optimizing the carbon loading.  As a high-level conductive plastic, the carbon-loading is such that it is high-enough to meet the electrical requirements needed for applications such as electrodes and pressure sensors.</p><p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series film and its conductivity are unaffected by humidity and age.  The film is heat-sealable, flexible and offers exceptional abrasion resistance.  The film gives good thermal stability and has outstanding chemical resistance. It has a standard thickness range from 65 micron to 100 micron (2.5 mil to 4 mil) and is available in sheeting, tubing, or bag versions.  Roll lengths and widths vary depending on thickness and application.</p>\r\n<h2>Applications for High-Level Electrically Conductive Plastic</h2><p>LINQSTAT XVCF-Series sheeting can be used for TENS Electrodes manufacturing as well as high-level precision pressure sensors.</p>', '<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is highly conductive volume conductive polyethylene film similar to our standard VCF-Series film but with a higher electrically conductive carbon loading in the polymer mix.  Having a surface resistance of less than 100 ohms per square (10E2 Ω/square), this extra loading makes the XVCF-Series more conductive than our standard film and allows it to be used in applications that require a lower resistivity.</p>\r\n<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ XVCF-Series conductive films are thin, lightweight and relatively inert.  Furthermore, they are are well suited for applications requiring electrochemical reactions, high conductivity or charge storage including but not limited to electrodes (ECG, TENS, Defibrillation and Iontophoresis), batteries (flat-cell zinc/manganese dioxide (MnO2), Lithium Ion and Lithium polymer), and digital (electronic) white boards.</p>\r\n<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series film and its conductivity are unaffected by humidity and age.  The film is heat-sealable, flexible and offers exceptional abrasion resistance.  The film gives good thermal stability and has outstanding chemical resistance. It has a standard thickness range from 65μm to 100μm (2.75 mil to 4 mil) and is available in various lengths, widths and thicknesses.</p>\r\n<h2>Product Applications</h2>\r\n<p>Given its low surface resistance, LINQSTAT XVCF-Series films have been successfully used as a pressure sensor making it useful for applications that require more conductivity to be able to detect more subtle pressure differences. For less-sensitive pressure sensor applications or applications that have larege surface areas and/or higher application pressures, CAPLINQ LINQSTAT VCF-Series may be sufficient.  Examples of applications that use the material as a pressure sensor is in the manufacture of digital whiteboards.</p>\r\n<p>Due to its low-resistivity and its resistance to a range of chemicals and alcohols, LINQSTAT XVCF-Series films are suitable for use in electrodes.  Its matte finish allows it to be printed on, and the low material thickness makes it flexible to adapt well to a range of contours.</p>\r\n<h2>Applications:</h2>\r\n<ul />\r\n<li>ECG electrodes</li>\r\n<li>TENS electrodes</li>\r\n<li>Defibrillation electrodes</li>\r\n<li>Digital white boards</li>\r\n<li>Lithium ion / polymer  battery</li>\r\n<li>Flat-cell MnO2 battery</li>\r\n\r\n<h2>PRODUCT FEATURES & BENEFITS:</h2> \r\n<li>Volume-conductive plastic</li>\r\n<li>Black Opaque - Printable</li>\r\n<li>Provides Anti-Static protection to electronics components</li>\r\n<li>Groundable</li>\r\n<li>Humidity independent conductivity</li>\r\n<li>Thin, Lightweight, Inert</li>\r\n\r\n<h2>CHEMICAL SUSCEPTIBILITY:</h2>\r\n<li>Methanol: Resistant</li>\r\n<li>Ethanol: Resistant</li>\r\n<li>Isopropanol: Resistant</li>\r\n<li>Weak Acids: Resistant</li>\r\n<li>Ketones (Acetone): Slow Attack</li>\r\n<li>Weak Alkalines: Slow Attack</li>\r\n<li>Hydrocarbons: Non-Resistant</li>\r\n\r\n<h2>PRODUCT NOMENCLATURE</h2>\r\n<li>X: eXtra Conductive</li>\r\n<li>VCF: Volume Conductive Film</li>'),
(466, 263, 'product_s_desc', '<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series is highly conductive volume conductive polyethylene film similar to our standard VCF-Series film but with a higher electrically conductive carbon loading in the polymer mix.  Having a surface resistance of less than 100 ohms per square (10E2 Ω/square), this extra loading makes the XVCF-Series more conductive than our standard film and allows it to be used in applications that require a lower resistivity.</p>\r\n<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT™ XVCF-Series conductive films are thin, lightweight and relatively inert.  Furthermore, they are are well suited for applications requiring electrochemical reactions, high conductivity or charge storage including but not limited to electrodes (ECG, TENS, Defibrillation and Iontophoresis), batteries (flat-cell zinc/manganese dioxide (MnO2), Lithium Ion and Lithium polymer), and digital (electronic) white boards.</p>\r\n<p>CAPLINQ LINQSTAT XVCF-Series film and its conductivity are unaffected by humidity and age.  The film is heat-sealable, flexible and offers exceptional abrasion resistance.  The film gives good thermal stability and has outstanding chemical resistance. It has a standard thickness range from 65μm to 100μm (2.75 mil to 4 mil) and is available in various lengths, widths and thicknesses.</p>\r\n<h2>Product Applications</h2>\r\n<p>Given its low surface resistance, LINQSTAT XVCF-Series films have been successfully used as a pressure sensor making it useful for applications that require more conductivity to be able to detect more subtle pressure differences. For less-sensitive pressure sensor applications or applications that have larege surface areas and/or higher application pressures, CAPLINQ LINQSTAT VCF-Series may be sufficient.  Examples of applications that use the material as a pressure sensor is in the manufacture of digital whiteboards.</p>\r\n<p>Due to its low-resistivity and its resistance to a range of chemicals and alcohols, LINQSTAT XVCF-Series films are 