(1473, 791, 'product_s_desc', 'LinqSil Aersosol Silicone-Based, 100% Non-Ozone Depleting 400ml can for Semiconductor, Electronics, Industrial and Automotive Applications.  Very competitive material and cheapest on the market. This solvent is to suspend the  particles for perfect mold release and  cleaning purposes.', '<p>LinqSil™ Series mold release agents are high-performance, high operating temperature mold release agents designed to release epoxy, epoxy mold compounds, polyurethane, polyester resins, EPDM, nitrile, thermoplastics and flexible or rigid integral foams from their molds.  Used extensively in the semiconductor passive device industry, LinqSil™ S-100 Series is an effective and versatile mold release agent for epoxy mold compounds.</p>\r\n<p>Despite being silicone-based, LinqSil™ S-100 Series mold release agent is completely compatible with epoxy molding compounds, as well as liquid hot- and cold-curing epoxy-, polyurethane and polyester resins.  For EPDM, Nitrile and thermoplastic molding, please refer to LinqSil S-200, and for flexible or rigid integral foams, please refer to LinqSil S-300.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Product Applications</h2>\r\n<ul>Current commercial applications of LinqSil S-100 include:\r\n<li>Epoxy Molding Compound Mold Release for Active Semiconductors (ICs, TQFPs, BGAs, etc.)</li>\r\n<li>Epoxy Molding Compound Mold Release for Passive Semiconductors (resistors, capacitors)</li>\r\n<li>Mold Release Agent for transformers, inductors, relays, and electro-medical applications</li>\r\n<li>New Mold Break-In</li>\r\n<li>Incomparable Part Release Characteristics</li>\r\n<li>Outstanding Rust Proofing Characteristics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>LinqSil S-100 has been designed not to char or burn at high temperatures, making it extremely well suited for high temperature molding.  It has been used successfully in applications running as hot as 200C.  Despite being extremely well suited to high temperature applications, no heat-treatment is required to activate the mold release, so it it equally well-suited to cold-curing or room-temperature curing chemistries.</p>\r\n<p>LinqSil S-100 can be used even with complicated moldings, to achieve perfect separation.  It builds on any mold, which is why expensive mold cleanings remain limited to a minimum. Contours and dimensional stability of the forms are not altered by LinqSil S-100. It is equally good for use on metal as well as plastic molds.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>LinqSil S-100 has an excellent lubricating effect which has three main benefits:\r\n<li>the life of the mold is prolonged</li>\r\n<li>the demolded parts have a beautiful finish surface</li>\r\n<li>very thin, or highly flexible or sensitive parts do not rip or tear on removal</li>\r\n\r\n<h2>Applications</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Epoxy Mold Compounds</li>\r\n<li>Polyurethane Resins</li>\r\n<li>Polyester Resins</li>\r\n<li>Hot- and cold-curing systems</li>\r\n<li>Semiconductor & Electronic</li>\r\n<li>Electrical & Medical</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Features & Benefits</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Silicone lubricant, tailored to transfer molding processes</li>\r\n<li>High Operating temperatures, high performance</li>\r\n<li>20 years succesful in very critical processes</li>\r\n<li>Works perfect with Epoxies, it does not mix at all!</li>\r\n<li>Very competitive pricing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Product Nomenclature</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>S: Silicone Based</li>\r\n<li>100: Epoxy, Polyurethane and Polyester resins</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(1474, 792, 'product_s_desc', '<h2>English</h2>\r\n<p>LinqSil S-100™ is a versatile, high performance and high operating temperature stable, silicone-based mold release agent suitable for most epoxy molding compounds, hot- and cold-cured epoxy, polyurethane and polyester resins.</p>\r\n<p>In order to have the best results during the production process, a thin uniform thickness of a layer of the LinqSil S-100™ mixture should be sprayed on the mold. The release agent has no build up on the mold and should show a shiny surface, when properly applied.</p>\r\n<h2>German</h2>\r\n<p>LinqSil S-100™  ist ein hochleistungs- und hochhitzebeständiges Formtrennmittel  auf der Grundlage von Siliconen Geeignet für die meisten Polyurethan-Elastomere, harte bis weich elastische integralschäume, Epoxid-, Polyesterharze, Kunststoffe und Polymere.</p>\r\n<p>Zur Erreichung optimaler Resultate im Produktionsprozess, eine dünne gleichmäßige Dicke von LinQSil S-100™  Mischung sollte auf die Formen-oberfläche  gesprüht werden. Das Trennmittel hast  kein Aufbau auf der Form und sollte eine glänzende Oberfläche, zeigen, wenn sie richtig angewendet wird.</p>\r\n<h2>French</h2>\r\n<p>LinqSil S-100™ est un haute performance agent de démoulage extrêment résistant aux températures élevées. Applicable pour la plupart des élastomeres de polyuréthane, des mousses de polyurethane à peau intégrée, flexibles à rigides, des resins epoxides et polyesters, plastiques et polymères.</p>\r\n<p>Pour avoir les meilleurs résultats pendant le proces de production, une fine épaisseur uniforme d''une couche du mélange LinqSil S-100™ doit être pulvérisée sur le moule. L''agent de libération a pas de s''accumuler sur le moule et devrait montrer une surface brillante, lorsqu''il est correctement appliqué.</p>', '<p>LinqSil S-100™ is a versatile, high performance and high operating temperature stable, silicone-based mold release agent suitable for most epoxy molding compounds, hot- and cold-cured epoxy, polyurethane and polyester resins.</p>\r\n<p>In order to have the best results during the production process, a thin uniform thickness of a layer of the LinqSil S-100™ mixture should be sprayed on the mold. The release agent has no build up on the mold and should show a shiny surface, when properly applied.</p>\r\n<p>Despite being silicone-based, LinqSil™ S-100 Series mold release agent is completely compatible with epoxy molding compounds, as well as liquid hot- and cold-curing epoxy-, polyurethane and polyester resins.  For EPDM, Nitrile and thermoplastic molding, please refer to LinqSil S-200, and for flexible or rigid integral foams, please refer to LinqSil S-300.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Product Applications</h2>\r\n<ul>Current commercial applications of LinqSil S-100 include:\r\n<li>Epoxy Molding Compound Mold Release for Active Semiconductors (ICs, TQFPs, BGAs, etc.)</li>\r\n<li>Epoxy Molding Compound Mold Release for Passive Semiconductors (resistors, capacitors)</li>\r\n<li>Mold Release Agent for transformers, inductors, relays, and electro-medical applications</li>\r\n<li>New Mold Break-In</li>\r\n<li>Incomparable Part Release Characteristics</li>\r\n<li>Outstanding Rust Proofing Characteristics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>LinqSil S-100 has been designed not to char or burn at high temperatures, making it extremely well suited for high temperature molding.  It has been used successfully in applications running as hot as 200C.  Despite being extremely well suited to high temperature applications, no heat-treatment is required to activate the mold release, so it it equally well-suited to cold-curing or room-temperature curing chemistries.</p>\r\n<p>LinqSil S-100 can be used even with complicated moldings, to achieve perfect separation.  It builds on any mold, which is why expensive mold cleanings remain limited to a minimum. Contours and dimensional stability of the forms are not altered by LinqSil S-100. It is equally good for use on metal as well as plastic molds.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>LinqSil S-100 has an excellent lubricating effect which has three main benefits:\r\n<li>the life of the mold is prolonged</li>\r\n<li>the demolded parts have a beautiful finish surface</li>\r\n<li>very thin, or highly flexible or sensitive parts do not rip or tear on removal</li>\r\n\r\n<h2>Applications</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Epoxy Mold Compounds</li>\r\n<li>Polyurethane Resins</li>\r\n<li>Polyester Resins</li>\r\n<li>Hot- and cold-curing systems</li>\r\n<li>Semiconductor & Electronic</li>\r\n<li>Electrical & Medical</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Features & Benefits</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Silicone lubricant, tailored to transfer molding processes</li>\r\n<li>High Operating temperatures, high performance</li>\r\n<li>20 years succesful in very critical processes</li>\r\n<li>Works perfect with Epoxies, it does not mix at all!</li>\r\n<li>Very competitive pricing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Product Nomenclature</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>S: Silicone Based</li>\r\n<li>100: Epoxy, Polyurethane and Polyester resins</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>German</h2>\r\n<p>LinqSil S-100™  ist ein hochleistungs- und hochhitzebeständiges Formtrennmittel  auf der Grundlage von Siliconen Geeignet für die meisten Polyurethan-Elastomere, harte bis weich elastische integralschäume, Epoxid-, Polyesterharze, Kunststoffe und Polymere.</p>\r\n<p>Zur Erreichung optimaler Resultate im Produktionsprozess, eine dünne gleichmäßige Dicke von LinQSil S-100™  Mischung sollte auf die Formen-oberfläche  gesprüht werden. Das Trennmittel hast  kein Aufbau auf der Form und sollte eine glänzende Oberfläche, zeigen, wenn sie richtig angewendet wird.</p>\r\n<h2>French</h2>\r\n<p>LinqSil S-100™ est un haute performance agent de démoulage extrêment résistant aux températures élevées. Applicable pour la plupart des élastomeres de polyuréthane, des mousses de polyurethane à peau intégrée, flexibles à rigides, des resins epoxides et polyesters, plastiques et polymères.</p>\r\n<p>Pour avoir les meilleurs résultats pendant le proces de production, une fine épaisseur uniforme d''une couche du mélange LinqSil S-100™ doit être pulvérisée sur le moule. L''agent de libération a pas de s''accumuler sur le moule et devrait montrer une surface brillante, lorsqu''il est correctement appliqué.</p>'),
