(1562, 833, 'product_s_desc', '', '<h2>The one powder solution for low and medium voltage busbar and switch gear applications</h2>\r\n<p>SolEpoxy™ DK15-0907 Red is an epoxy based, "One Powder Solution" coating powder developed for low and medium voltage (600V - 38,000V) bus bars.  Used for over 20 years by major power distribution companies for low and medium-voltage bus bar applications, DK15-0907 provides a smooth surface appearance with high edge coverage.  The fusion bonded coating is smooth, tough, and moisture resistant for applications up to 38 KV. <a href="http://data.ul.com/link/plastics.aspx?PR=PYLNAKMIFDBCPFVRRGVRRROEPQDSCLGR">DK15-0907 is UL recognized</a> for UL94-V0 rating and meets the UL746B Relative Thermal Index (RTI) of 130°C and is currently on-test for an RTI at or above 150°C. Rapid and thick build reduces production cycle times. Particle size is optimized for the fluidized bed coating process.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Advantages of DK15-0907 for Busbar Coating</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>One powder for low and medium voltage busbars</li>\r\n<li>Used for more than 15 years by major power distribution companies</li>\r\n<li>Suitable for copper and aluminum bar</li>\r\n<li>Smooth, uniform coating build in excess of 200 mils (5 mm)</li>\r\n<li>Rapid build rates to reduce cycle times</li>\r\n<li>Productivity support including:</li>\r\n<li>Fine grind powder to replenish size distribution</li>\r\n<li>Fluidizing agent to promote uniform build</li>\r\n<li>Ongoing testing to optimize quality & productivity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Typical applications and uses of {product_name} include:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Low Voltage (600V) Copper, Aluminum and Brass Busbars</li>\r\n<li>Medium Voltage (up to 38kV) Copper, Aluminum and Brass Busbars</li>\r\n<li>Switchgear Equipment for Power Distribution</li>\r\n</ul>'),
