(1573, 840, 'product_s_desc', '<h2>A uniquely flexible insulating coating powder for high voltage fuses, lightning arrestors, low voltage busbars and other niche applications</h2>\r\n<p>SolEpoxy™ DK52 is a flexible, moisture resistant epoxy coating powder developed for the insulation of high voltage fuses, axial leaded fuses, and other high voltage electrical apparatus. It offers very high flexibility, which provides maximum efficiency of low voltage busbar designs, which can often involve complex shapes. Besides being very flexible, DK15-200E carries a UL recognition (RTI) for 100,000 hours at 105°C making it ideal for applications requiring high thermal stability.  The fusion bonded coating is smooth, tough, and moisture resistant for applications up to 600V. <a href="http://data.ul.com/link/plastics.aspx?PR=PYLNAKMIFDBCPFVRRGVRRROEPQDSCLGR">DK15-2000E is UL recognized</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Advantages of DK15-2000E for High Voltage Fuses and other Niche Applications</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Very flexible epoxy coating powder</li>\r\n<li>High voltage fuses and low voltage busbars</li>\r\n<li>Very high dielectric strength</li>\r\n<li>Meets minimum RTI rating</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Typical applications and uses of {product_name} include:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Low Voltage (600V) Copper, Aluminum and Brass Busbars</li>\r\n<li>High Voltage Fuse Coating</li>\r\n<li>Leaded Axial Fuse Coating</li>\r\n<li>Lighting Arrestors</li>\r\n<li>Switchgear Equipment for Power Distribution</li>\r\n</ul>', '<h2>A uniquely flexible insulating coating powder for high voltage fuses, lightning arrestors, low voltage busbars and other niche applications</h2>\r\n<p>SolEpoxy™ DK15-2000E is a flexible, moisture resistant epoxy coating powder developed for the insulation of high voltage fuses, axial leaded fuses, and other high voltage electrical apparatus. It offers very high flexibility, which provides maximum efficiency of low voltage busbar designs, which can often involve complex shapes. Besides being very flexible, DK15-200E carries a UL recognition (RTI) for 100,000 hours at 105°C making it ideal for applications requiring high thermal stability.  The fusion bonded coating is smooth, tough, and moisture resistant for applications up to 600V. <a href="http://data.ul.com/link/plastics.aspx?PR=PYLNAKMIFDBCPFVRRGVRRROEPQDSCLGR">DK15-2000E is UL recognized</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Advantages of DK15-2000E for High Voltage Fuses and other Niche Applications</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Very flexible epoxy coating powder</li>\r\n<li>High voltage fuses and low voltage busbars</li>\r\n<li>Very high dielectric strength</li>\r\n<li>Meets minimum RTI rating</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Typical applications and uses of {product_name} include:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Low Voltage (600V) Copper, Aluminum and Brass Busbars</li>\r\n<li>High Voltage Fuse Coating</li>\r\n<li>Leaded Axial Fuse Coating</li>\r\n<li>Lighting Arrestors</li>\r\n<li>Switchgear Equipment for Power Distribution</li>\r\n</ul>'),
