(1678, 883, 'product_s_desc', '<h2>Reliable, Low-Cost, Single-Use USB Temperature Logger for Easy Monitoring of Logistics Cold Chain</h2>\r\n<p>CAPLINQ introduces TempMatSolEpoxy™ DK15-0606 Tan is an epoxy based, "One Powder Solution" coating powder developed for low and medium voltage (600V - 38,000V) bus bars.  Used for over 20 years by major power distribution companies for low and medium-voltage bus bar applications, DK15-0606 provides a smooth surface appearance with high edge coverage.  The fusion bonded coating is smooth, tough, and moisture resistant for applications up to 38 KV. <a href="http://data.ul.com/link/plastics.aspx?PR=PYLNAKMIFDBCPFVRRGVRRROEPQDSCLGR">DK15-0606 is UL recognized</a> for UL94-V0 rating and meets the UL746B Relative Thermal Index (RTI) of 130°C and is currently on-test for an RTI at or above 150°C. Rapid and thick build reduces production cycle times. Particle size is optimized for the fluidized bed coating process.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Advantages of DK15-0606 for Busbar Coating</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>One powder for low and medium voltage busbars</li>\r\n<li>Used for more than 15 years by major power distribution companies</li>\r\n<li>Suitable for copper and aluminum bar</li>\r\n<li>Smooth, uniform coating build in excess of 200 mils (5 mm)</li>\r\n<li>Rapid build rates to reduce cycle times</li>\r\n<li>Productivity support including:</li>\r\n<li>Fine grind powder to replenish size distribution</li>\r\n<li>Fluidizing agent to promote uniform build</li>\r\n<li>Ongoing testing to optimize quality & productivity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Typical applications and uses of {product_name} include:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Low Voltage (600V) Copper, Aluminum and Brass Busbars</li>\r\n<li>Medium Voltage (up to 38kV) Copper, Aluminum and Brass Busbars</li>\r\n<li>Switchgear Equipment for Power Distribution</li>\r\n</ul>', '<h2>Reliable, Low-Cost, Single-Use USB Temperature Logger for Easy Monitoring of Logistics Cold Chain</h2>\r\n<p>CAPLINQ introduces TempMate®, your reliable, low-cost solution for your refrigerated or frozen supply chain.  The package couldn''t be more simple - just press and go!  Packaged in a simple-to-use, package\r\n\r\nhain SupplyUSB PDF-loggers by Escort offer you an economical solution for logging your temperature data. The Mini-USB PDF-logger is meant for single use, easily activated by pressing the button, or on timer through software. The output is reported in PDF and no special software is needed.\r\n\r\nThe logger is applicable for temperatures ranging from -40℃ until +80℃, it has a very high accuracy rate and can hold up to 8000 readings.\r\n\r\nA led light ﬂashes red for high, blue for low and green for ok to give you the opportunity to respond immediately if necessary.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Advantages of DK15-0606 for Busbar Coating</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>One powder for low and medium voltage busbars</li>\r\n<li>Used for more than 15 years by major power distribution companies</li>\r\n<li>Suitable for copper and aluminum bar</li>\r\n<li>Smooth, uniform coating build in excess of 200 mils (5 mm)</li>\r\n<li>Rapid build rates to reduce cycle times</li>\r\n<li>Productivity support including:</li>\r\n<li>Fine grind powder to replenish size distribution</li>\r\n<li>Fluidizing agent to promote uniform build</li>\r\n<li>Ongoing testing to optimize quality & productivity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Typical applications and uses of {product_name} include:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Low Voltage (600V) Copper, Aluminum and Brass Busbars</li>\r\n<li>Medium Voltage (up to 38kV) Copper, Aluminum and Brass Busbars</li>\r\n<li>Switchgear Equipment for Power Distribution</li>\r\n</ul>'),
